<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>High School! Kimengumi is a manga series written by Motoei Shinzawa which ran in Weekly Shonen Jump from 1982 to 1987. Kimengumi is an episodic chronicle of the bizarre adventures of a group of misfit junior high school (and later, high school) boys who form a club known as the "Kimengumi".
                  <br><br>The Playstation game is a Table Hockey game that features characters from the manga. The player can choose (at first time) from one of the 5 main characters and have to defeat different characters in the story mode to unlock the gallery mode. The gameplay the player that reach 7 goals first win the match or have more goals than the other at the end of the time. There are also special attacks and special items to active them.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Gag cartoon legend "High School! Set Noodle" was a table hockey game? Total of 11 people big success familiar characters! Mortal and interesting stage, etc. sidesplitting gags, such as voice actors and animation with graphics! Table hockey tournament prize is only fine Chie-chan! ? We wish the plane set of odd faces ready to defend two or victory! ?
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>First person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Table Hockey & Anime themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

